  - genomic_pos (genomic position): {'chr': '1', 'end': 173207331, 'ensemblgene': 'ENSG00000117586', 'start': 173183731, 'strand': -1}
  - name (gene name): TNF superfamily member 4
  - summary (protein summary text): This gene encodes a cytokine of the tumor necrosis factor (TNF) ligand family. The encoded protein functions in T cell antigen-presenting cell (APC) interactions and mediates adhesion of activated T cells to endothelial cells. Polymorphisms in this gene have been associated with Sjogren's syndrome and systemic lupus erythematosus. Alternative splicing results in multiple transcript variants. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2014].

